Title: CI/CD with GitHub Actions: Build & Push Docker Images to Docker Hub
Description:
Hi there! Today we are going to see how to build and push a Docker image to Docker Hub, as part of your CI/CD pipeline, using GitHub Workflows.

yaml file:

name: Build and push to Dockerhub

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
    
jobs:
  push:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    
    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v4
        
      - name: Login
        uses: docker/login-action@v3.3.0
        with:
          username: ${{ secrets.DOCKER_USERNAME }}
          password: ${{ secrets.DOCKER_PASSWORD }}
          
      - name: Build and push Docker image
        uses: docker/build-push-action@v6.13.0
        with:
          context: .
          file: ./Weather.Api/Dockerfile
          push: true
          tags: |
            repo-name:${{ github.sha }}
            repo-name/weather-api:latest

Title: Explicit Includes: The Art of Fetching Just Enough Data in EF Core - Chris Woody Woodruff
Description: If you‚Äôve ever gone grocery shopping while hungry, you know how easy it is to end up with more than you need. The same thing happens in EF Core when you‚Äôre too eager with your Include statements‚Äîyou fetch all the data, even the stuff you don‚Äôt need, and suddenly, your app feels sluggish. That‚Äôs where Explicit Includes comes in, allowing you to fetch only what you need when needed, making your development process more efficient. Think of it as grocery shopping with a list, but for your code.
